$ ORA-02063: preceding … from

*ORA-02063* is thrown if a remote datatabase involved in a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/link throws an error.

{ Selecting from an inexisting table over a database link

  Trying to select from an inexisting table over a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/link results in an *ORA-02063: preceding line from dblinkname* error:
code {
select * from inexisting_table@abc.xyz
-- → development/databases/Oracle/errors/ORA-00942_table-or-view-does-not-exist
-- ORA-02063: preceding line from ABC
code }

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/errors[Other Oracle error messages]
